{%- doc -%}
  Per-instance MOBILE (≤749px) font-size override. Render this in the block BODY.

  Pairs with a `font_size_mobile` select (empty = inherit the desktop size). When a value
  is chosen, the target element must also carry `mobile-font-{{ id }}` so this scoped rule
  (emitted after head CSS) overrides the preset/custom desktop size on mobile only. The
  class is intentionally doubled to reach specificity (0,3,1 on the child, 0,2,0 on the
  element itself), beating native preset selectors (`.text-block.h2 > *`, `.h3.h3`,
  `.paragraph.paragraph`) in either layout — no `!important` needed. Emits nothing when the
  value is blank, leaving the native responsive sizing intact.

  @param {string} value - chosen font-size (e.g. '1rem'); blank = no override (inherit desktop)
  @param {string} id - a unique id, e.g. block.id

  @example
  {% render 'mobile-typography', value: block.settings.font_size_mobile, id: block.id %}
{%- enddoc -%}

{%- if value != blank -%}
  {%- style -%}
    @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
      .mobile-font-{{ id }}.mobile-font-{{ id }},
      .mobile-font-{{ id }}.mobile-font-{{ id }} > * {
        font-size: {{ value }};
      }
    }
  {%- endstyle -%}
{%- endif -%}
